WEBVTT

00:00:00.880 --> 00:00:05.040
Here are three new features that give you even more control on Positive Connect Cloud.

00:00:05.040 --> 00:00:10.000
Number one, for the first time you can deploy programmatically from the RStudio IDE or any R

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.720
session thanks to new support in the RSConnect package. For instance, let's look at this

00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:21.200
Quarto document that we're working on that scrapes data from ESPN.com. I can use the RSConnect package

00:00:21.200 --> 00:00:27.120
to say Connect Cloud User. This is going to kick off a handshake with Connect Cloud.

00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:31.600
I'm going to authorize access, and then I'm going to be able to go back into the IDE to

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:37.599
continue with the deployment. Once here, I can pick which account that I want,

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:44.639
and I can use another RSConnect command, deploy app, to put this onto Connect Cloud. It's going

00:00:44.639 --> 00:00:49.759
to confirm which account that I want. So we'll go to Connect Cloud, we'll do our deployment,

00:00:49.759 --> 00:00:52.799
we'll get all of the dependencies that are needed from our local environment,

00:00:53.360 --> 00:00:59.680
and now we're going to be able to see this show up on Connect Cloud. And here's the final document.

00:01:01.919 --> 00:01:08.239
Number two, set fine-grained compute and runtime settings. So let's go into a Shiny application.

00:01:09.279 --> 00:01:13.839
This is an A-B test calculator. If I increase the number of conversions on the B side,

00:01:13.839 --> 00:01:17.760
we're going to see all of a sudden we have statistical significance. But I can also go

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:23.279
into edit settings, and we're going to see a bunch of new tabs, one for compute. Now,

00:01:23.279 --> 00:01:27.839
this is going to control the memory and the CPU allocated to both your deployment and when the

00:01:27.839 --> 00:01:33.519
application is running. You can also control runtime settings for application workers and

00:01:33.519 --> 00:01:37.919
connections. These give you control over how your application runs and scales for concurrent

00:01:37.919 --> 00:01:45.279
requests and users. Any changes made here do require a republish. Feature number three,

00:01:45.279 --> 00:01:49.599
users on paid plans can schedule automated content republishing. Let's go back to our

00:01:49.599 --> 00:01:56.639
initial quarto document. If I go into schedule, I can select to enable a schedule for this piece

00:01:56.639 --> 00:02:04.800
of content. Confirm that I'm looking at East Coast United States. Maybe I want weekly on Monday,

00:02:04.800 --> 00:02:14.960
Wednesday, and Friday. And let's set this to 5.30 p.m. I save this, and I'm ready for the

00:02:14.960 --> 00:02:20.479
schedule to repeat at those time intervals. There you have it, three new features to give

00:02:20.479 --> 00:02:22.880
you more control on Connect Cloud.

